  <article>
    <h3>About us</h3>

    <p>
      Afghan Mobile Reconstruction Association (AMRAN) is a registered Afghan
      development non-governmental and non-profit organization. Established in
      1990, it has assisted and contributed towards the improvement of social
      and economic conditions of Afghans.
    </p>
    <p>
      AMRAN has implemented more than 300 projects in partnership with several
      UN, USAID and other foreign donor agencies.
    </p>
    <h4>
      It has experiences in the following fields.
    </h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Training and Development</li>
      <li>Employment Related Services</li>
      <li>Humanitarian services</li>
      <li>Health Services</li>
      <li>Agricultural Services</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <article>
    <h3>
      Vision / Mission/ Core Values
    </h3>

    <p>
      <strong> Vision: </strong> AMRAN vision is to see a developed Afghanistan
      with every person has equal rights to live in this world with dignity.
    </p>
    <p>
